remainder /rɪˈmeɪndə/

1. QUANT The remainder of a group are the things or people that still remain after the other things or people have gone or have been dealt with. 剩余部分 [QUANT 'of' def-n] 

例： He gulped down the remainder of his coffee. 他一口喝完了剩下的咖啡。 

2. PRON Remainder is also a pronoun. 剩余部分 

例： Only 5.9 percent of the area is now covered in trees. Most of the remainder is farmland. 该地区现在的树木覆盖率仅为5.9％。剩余部分大多是农田。

